dct_title_s: Tabulam hanc Aegypti, si æquus ac Diligens Lector, cum Alys, quæ Hactenus Prodicūt
dct_description_sm: Bar scale on map given in "Milliarium Italica."
Decorative cartouche, compass rose, ships, sea monsters and other fauna.
Shows topography, vegetation, small bird's eye views of cities, waterways, ports.
Lower and upper halves of map appear separately, each with a containing border.
Appears in Bry's Petits voyages, part I, 1606.
